    <section id="maintenance" class="maintenance-section-lmn234">
        <div class="container-bcd890">
            <h2 class="section-title-efg123">Maintenance Tips</h2>
            <div class="maintenance-tips-opq567">
                <div class="tip-card-rst890">
                    <h4>Regular Cleaning</h4>
                    <p>Sweep your patio weekly and wash with mild soap and water monthly. This prevents buildup of dirt and organic matter that can cause staining or damage.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="tip-card-rst890">
                    <h4>Weed Prevention</h4>
                    <p>Apply polymeric sand between pavers and use pre-emergent herbicides in spring. Regular maintenance prevents weeds from establishing in joints.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="tip-card-rst890">
                    <h4>Seasonal Inspection</h4>
                    <p>Check for loose pavers, cracks, or drainage issues twice yearly. Early detection and repair prevent minor issues from becoming major problems.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="tip-card-rst890">
                    <h4>Sealing Schedule</h4>
                    <p>Most patios benefit from sealing every 2-3 years. This protects against stains, weather damage, and helps maintain color vibrancy.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="tip-card-rst890">
                    <h4>Winter Protection</h4>
                    <p>Remove snow promptly and avoid using salt-based deicers. Use sand for traction and plastic shovels to prevent surface scratching.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="tip-card-rst890">
                    <h4>Furniture Care</h4>
                    <p>Use furniture pads to prevent scratching and move pieces occasionally to prevent permanent indentations or discoloration patterns.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

